   {c\alpha  + d\beta }  \cr 

 } } \right] = \left[ {\matrix{
   \alpha   \cr 
   \beta   \cr 

 } } \right]$$$$ \Rightarrow $$ $$\eqalign{
  &amp; a\alpha  + b\beta  = \alpha \,......(1)  \cr 
  &amp; c\alpha  + d\beta  = \beta \,......(2) \cr} $$<br><br>$$\alpha (a - 1) =  - b\beta $$ and $$c\alpha  = \beta (1 - d)$$<br><br>$${\alpha  \over \beta } = {{ - b} \over {a - 1}}$$ &amp; $${\alpha  \over \beta } = {{1 - d} \over c}$$<br><br>$$ \therefore $$ $${{ - b} \over {a - 1}} = {{1 - d} \over c}$$<br><br>$$ - bc = (a - 1)(1 - d)$$<br><br>$$ - bc = a - ad - 1 + d$$<br><br>$$ad - bc = a + d - 1$$<br><br>$$ = 2021 - 1 = 2020$$

